This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a deep learning-based method for unsupervised learning of multiple shared representations. It also addresses optimization challenges through Multi-Task Bayesian Optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the proposed method involves learning shared representations from multiple data sources, which is a common task in AI. 

The paper could also be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves predicting unknown entries in matrices, which is a common task in recommendation systems. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the proposed method can be used to integrate heterogeneous data sources, which is a common task in network analysis. 

Finally, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper addresses optimization challenges in learning shared representations, which involves designing efficient algorithms.
